<h2>Announcement: Submit Your Everquest Guide!</h2>&nbsp;posted&nbsp;Sunday, July 25, 2004 9:57 AM EDT (  <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/printnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/print.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Printer Friendly Page" /></a> <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/cgi-bin/admin/sendnews.cgi?newsid1090767465,499," target="_blank"><img src="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/templates/1/images/mail.gif" height="11" width="15" border="0" alt="Send this Article to a Friend" /></a> )<br />You can now submit your <b>EQ Guide</b> to us on our <a href="http://www.everquest-online.com/content/everquest-addguide.php" class="newslink">Add Guide page</a>. Special rewards for unique and thorough guides. Please submit your personal work only, do not copy someone else's guide.<br /><br /><div align="center"><h1>EQ Everquest News</h1></div>
<br />
<h2>Account and Technical
  Phone Support Closed Wednesday, December 6th</h2><br /><br> <p>Account and Technical Phone Support will be closed on Wednesday, December 6th. Phone support will return at its normal hours 10:00am through 7:00pm PST on Thursday December 7th. .</p> <p>Account and Technical Live Chat support will remain available during its normal hours Monday through Friday, 10:00am through 7:00pm PST at http://station.sony.com/chat.</p> <p>Account and Technical Email support is available any time at http://station.sony.com/email.</p> <p>Our Account and Technical Support knowledgebase is always available at http://station.sony.com/kb.</p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge &#150; November 30, 2006</h2><br /><P>&nbsp;</P>  <P>Nodyin joins in a new discusson about
  the Hot Zone changes coming in the update on December 5th, 2006.&nbsp; Read what he has to say
  <A HREF="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=331019&amp;view=by_date_ascending&amp;page=1">here</A>.</P>  <P>Prathun offers some information about
  the creation of the Demiplane events.&nbsp;
  Get the information <A HREF="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=331062#M331062">here</A>.</P>  <P>Rashere discussed the Drakkin breath
  weapon and responds to requests for similar abilities being given to other
  races.&nbsp; See his comments <A HREF="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=330314#M330314">here</A>.</P>  <P>In this week's edition of <A HREF="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&amp;message.id=10481&amp;jump=true">Ky's
  Chatter Box</A>: What
  was the cause of your most recent in-game death?</P>  <P>While
  visiting Cobalt Scar you encounter an Othmir who is missing a good chunk of
  fur from his backside.&nbsp; He invites you to join him for dinner and as you
  sit by a campfire later that evening he tells you the story of what happened
  to his backside.&nbsp; What was his story? Tell the
  Othmir&#146;s story in this week's <A HREF="http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&amp;message.id=10488">Creative
  Writing thread</A>.</P>  &nbsp;
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge RiffRaff &#150; November 30,
   2006</h2><br /><br> Real life first name: Per Martin<br> Main Character name: Merpa<br> Server: Saryrn (mith marr)<br> Guild: Basium ab Letum<br> <br> Where in the real life world do you live?Oslo, Norway<br> <br> How long have you played EQ? since january 2001<br> <br> What other MMOs have you played? EVE, Anarchy Online, StarWars Galaxies<br> <br> What type of work do you do? I work in a bookstore<br> <br> How long is your typical gaming session when playing EQ? Everything from 30 minutes to 5 hours<br> <br> What does a typical EQ day consist of for you? Just now trying to raise skill in tailoring, smithing and brewing, but questing and exping alot too.<br> <br> What was the race and class of your very first character? Wood Elf Ranger<br> <br> What got you into gaming and what sort of games do you like the most? Fun to do alone and with friends. I like RPG most but space games like Freelancer and EVE are great too. <br> <br> What other hobbies or activities do you take part in, other then playing EverQuest? Hunting, bicycling, fishing and other outdoor activities.<br> <br> What is your highest level in EQ? 72<br> <br> What race and class is your main character? Wood elf Druid<br> <br> What do you like the most about the class you have chosen for your main character? I can do everything with my druid, it suits me because i like to be able to do alot of different things.<br> <br> Does your main character worship a deity? Tunare<br> <br> How did you choose your main character's name? Rewright of real name, it s bad and i see now that should have chosen another name or used the name generator.<br> <br> Which classes in EQ have you NOT played? I have leveld all types of classes up to about 10.<br> <br> What is your favorite expansion? TSS<br> <br> What is your favorite zone? Jaggedpine Forrest for the varity in levels of monster. A player can stay here from early 40 to late 50. And when the zone came live the graphic was stunning. I also like the faction hits for animals, keeps me remembering that I am a druid.<br> <br> What is your favorite npc? Quillmane, this flying horse is almost an obsession, and I have killed him at least 20 times.<br> <br> Which expansion do you like the least? I dont play GoD much, because of the lack of solocontent, but i dont know enough of it to dislike it.<br> <br> Which zone do you like the least? Skyfire, i really hate dispelling mobs.<br> <br> Which npc do you like the least? Right now A cracked earthshaker in RCoD because he s a difficult mob to beat and I want my epic 1.5.<br> <br> What is the most platinum you have ever spent on purchasing a single item for one of your characters? I dont remember exact amount but approx. 40k perhaps on some PoP armor. Alot of platinum on tradeskillitems too.<br> <br> Do you have an item you no longer use but keep around for nostalgic reasons? If so what is it and why do you keep it? Warden of Tunare Symbol. A great item and a very good quest in Lesser Faydark. I used it from level 37 to mid 50s.<br> <br> What do you like best about EverQuest? The variety of the game. Always things to do and more things to do to develop my character. <br> <br> What do you get out of playing EverQuest? Fun, and great relaxation from a stressful everydaylife. I also enjoy to help other players.<br> <br> Describe your best experience from playing EverQuest? Difficult to find one, I have several. One time in a GM event me and my group won and names was broadcasted serverwide. I won Earring of the Frozen Skull with Divine Aura effect. One of my proudest moments in EQ. I also find great pleasure when difficult quests are finished. Like epic 1.0, Nature walkers scimitar, a quest I used more than 1 year to finish.<br> <br> Do you run or work for an EverQuest Fan Site? No<br>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Don&#146;t miss out on
  EverQuest Newsletters or Email from SOE!</h2><br /><br>We have a few emails that will be sent out soon that you don't want to miss! Make sure you are signed up to recieve newsletters and other important emails from SOE. What's included when you sign up?<br><br>You'll receive the quarterly Newsletters for the games you are signed up for.<br>You'll receive any promotional emails that we send out<br><br>To make sure you receive the next newsletter, do the following: <br><br>Click on My Account in the Station.com header<br>Click on Email Newsletters<br>Select those you wish to receive<br>Click on Make Changes (If you aren't sure you are getting the emails, click on Make Changes even if you don't change anything, just to refresh the setting.)<br>Or you can just visit https://secure.station.sony.com/optin/viewOptins.m<br> <br>How come I never seem to get any of the emails?<br><br>There are a couple of reasons you may not be receiving the emails from SOE:<br><br>You need to update your Email Address:<br>An incorrect Email Address is a common reason for not receiving the emails from the station. To update your email address, go to My Account in the Station.com header, select Registration, update your email address, make sure the box for "Check here to receive future Station e-mails with announcements of new games, contests, and more" is checked and Accept changes.</br></br>Email sent by SOE is being blocked:</br>If your e-mail system has a block, junk, bulk, or spam mail folder, you'll want to make sure that it allows e-mail from The Station@sony.com [station-mailer@sony-online.com]. You will need to check the options, properties, or preferences of your mail system to determine how to set this up.</br></br>Options not saved:</br>There's a chance that your options were not set correctly when the system changed over to this system. To fix this, click on the [Clear-All] link and click on Make Changes. Then select your options again and click on Make Changes again. That should refresh the list.</br>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Announcing the Ninth
  Official SOE Podcast!</h2><br />  <p>Tune in to the Ninth Official SOE Podcast. We hope you all enjoy the latest installment of our podcast series. Make sure to let us know how you like it! You can fire off an email to us at <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/mailto:feedback@soe.sony.com">feedback@soe.sony.com</a> or head over to the <a href="http://forums.station.sony.com/station/posts/list.m?topic_id=11500000607" target=_blank>Show Notes</a> and give us your comments.<p>You can download the MP3 file directly or subscribe to the RSS feed by clicking the button listed below. We have high and low bandwidth versions of the podcast available.</p>   <a href="http://download.station.sony.com/patch/web/misc/Podcast09_128k.mp3">High-Bandwidth</a> | <a href="http://community.station.sony.com/podcast/SOE_cast_lrg.xml"></a> <a href="http://download.station.sony.com/patch/web/misc/Podcast09_64k.mp3">Low-Bandwidth</a> | <a href="http://community.station.sony.com/podcast/SOE_cast_sml.xml"></a> <p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>November Forum Challenge
  &#150; November 20, 2006</h2><br /><br> <p>This week in the US, many people will be celebrating Thanksgiving with family and eating awesome food like: turkey, ham, mashed potatoes with gravy, stuffing, pumpkin pie and lots of other good stuff. Many cultures around the world celebrate similar holidays centered on harvest time.</p> <p>The forum challenge for November is to post a recipe and picture from your culture that is used to celebrate harvest time. (It does not necessarily have to be a recipe your family serves)</p> <p>The categories for this challenge will be: </p> Most unusual recipe<br> Most appealing recipe<br> Recipe most likely to have the most leftovers if served in your house<br> <br> <p>The Harvest Challenge will start today as of this post and run through Monday, November 27th at noon PST. You may submit your recipe and picture to cdelzer@soe.sony.com. Please include your forum handle and what culture uses this recipe for its harvest celebration as well as the category you wish to submit your recipe in.</p> <p>On Monday, November 27th sometimes after noon PST, I will post the recipes on the <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board?board.id=Fun">Just for Fun forum</a> and start a poll for each category so the community can vote on the recipes. One challenge winner from each category will receive a special forum title and an in-game prize for one character of their choice.</p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Tech and Account Phone
  Support Closed 11/23 and 11/24</h2><br /><br> <p>Tech and Account Phone support will be unavailable on Thursday November 23rd and Friday November 24th in observance of the holiday.</p> <p>Chat support will be available during its normal time Monday through Friday 10am through 7pm PST at station.sony.com/chat.</p> <p>Email support is always available at station.sony.com/email.</p> <p>Our Self-help knowledgebase is also available at station.sony.com/kb with answers to your questions.</p> <p>Phone support will return on Monday November 27th at its normal hours Monday through Friday 10am through 7pm PST.</p>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Sony Online
  Entertainment Games Available Through T-Mobile HotSpot!</h2><br /><br> <p>Beginning today, Monday, November 20, you can download EverQuest II, EverQuest, PlanetSide, and The Matrix Online at no cost with your T-Mobile HotSpot subscription! There are two packages available to subscribers.</p> <p>Gaming Pack Offer<br> T-mobile offers new subscribers to their HotSpot service the ability to download EQ, EQII, PS, and MxO at no cost and play for up to 30 days for free.</p> <p>Gamer on the Go Offer<br> T-mobile will allow subscribers of any SOE subscription based PC game to use their HotSpot service to play SOE games for $4.99/month (does not include SOE subscription price)</p> <p>You can visit the <a target="_blank" href="https://selfcare.hotspot.t-mobile.com/accountcreate/ExternalSetPromotionCode.do?promo=SOETWB96">T-Mobile HotSpot website</a> for more information on the promotion and the <a target="_blank" href="http://www.station.sony.com/promotions/T-Mobile">SOE Station website</a> for information on games and game keys.</p> 
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge &#150; November 16, 2006</h2><br /><br>Ngreth answers tradeskillers pleas to increase stacking on some of their more commonly used tradeskill itmes. To see what will increase or to submit itmes you would like to see increased you can follow<a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&message.id=17320&view=by_date_ascending&page=1"> this thread</a>.<br><br>CurtEQ, one of the EQ programmers, let the community know that he found and fixed the Demiplane of Blood instance crashing due to charm and death. You can read more about it <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=326423#M326423">here</a>.<br><br>Maddoc talks a little bit about the Reintroduction of boats coming soon. Read what he has to say <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=325917#M325917">here</a>.<br><br>Nodyin informs the community that new hot zones have been selected and are almost ready to go. Find out more <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=325060#M325060">here</a>.<br><br>In this week's edition of <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&message.id=10447&jump=true">Ky's Chatter Box</a>: How much platinum have you spent in the Shadowhaven Casino? <br><br>While walking through the forest in Lesser Faydwar you are suddenly surrounded by fairies who start pulling your hair, rifling through your backpacks and bags, untie any ties on your armor and just generally being a nuisance. You realize that if you don't do something quick these curious forest sprites will wreak total havoc on you and your equipment so you... Finish this scenarion in this week's <a href="http://eqplayers.station.sony.com/ http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Fun&message.id=10452&jump=true">Creative Writing thread</a>.
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
		<br /><h2>Halfling
  Hodgepodge RiffRaff &#150; November 16,
   2006</h2><br /><br> Real life first name: Mike<br> Forum handle: Skaterrat<br> Main Character name: Issack Knewton<br> Server: The Nameless<br> Guild: Euphoria<br> <br> Where in the real life world do you live? Alpharetta GA, 15min North of Atlanta<br> <br> How long have you played EQ? 5 years<br> <br> What other MMOs have you played? WOW, lineage 2<br> <br> What type of work do you do? Manufacturing<br> <br> How long is your typical gaming session when playing EQ? 4-6 hours<br> <br> What does a typical EQ day consist of for you? Raiding and finding recruits for the guild.<br> <br> What was the race and class of your very first character? Wood Elf Ranger<br> <br> What got you into gaming and what sort of games do you like the most? I been gaming since I was about 5y/o. I remember playing Pac Man with my brother, sister, and mom on the Atari VCS.<br> <br> What other hobbies or activities do you take part in, other then playing EverQuest? I play the guitar, and also like to read books.<br> <br> What is your highest level in EQ? 75 with 700+ aa and gaining aa every day<br> <br> What race and class is your main character? Dwarf Paladin<br> <br> What do you like the most about the class you have chosen for your main character? The ability to tank. Spot heal was the main reason why I created him.<br> <br> Does your main character worship a deity? Brell<br> <br> How did you choose your main character's name? At the Time, Paladins were knows as Sir, and Sir Issack Knewton fit the dwarf paladin well.<br> <br> Which classes in EQ have you NOT played? Bard<br> <br> What is your favorite expansion? POP<br> <br> What is your favorite zone? The old Veeshans Peek, before revamp and TL? Gate out was allowed.<br> <br> What is your favorite npc? Hatchet in Demi, it's such a fun event.<br> <br> Which expansion do you like the least? LOY. That expansion was pointless. I don't think I ever did any XP in any of the zones.<br> <br> Which zone do you like the least? Any zone with a AE debuff that cant be cured or blocked by a quest.<br> <br> Which npc do you like the least? Portios cat. He's a pain in the neck.<br> <br> What is the most platinum you have ever spent on purchasing a single item for one of your characters?400k<br> <br> Do you have an item you no longer use but keep around for nostalgic reasons? If so what is it and why do you keep it? Resplendent War Maul. It was the first weapon I received that was acquired by my guild. I also have every single weapon I have ever received from raids by my guild.<br> <br> What do you like best about EverQuest? The social aspect and raiding with friends, getting together and kicking butt.<br> <br> What do you get out of playing EverQuest? Relaxation from a hard day at work.<br> <br> Describe your best experience from playing EverQuest? The first time we kill a raid mob. The feeling of excitement and accomplishment.<br> <br> Do you run or work for an EverQuest Fan Site? nope.<br>
										  
										
																								
						  
						
						
